Date: 0/0/1927
Source: Me and Gus
Author: ANTHONY
Vol / Page: 73
Edition:
Quote: ... a boy along to help Gus on the stack, but he said `No', a man should be able to build a round stack on his pat, and he didn't want any boy standing about in the way while he was working.
Notes: a1927 Anthony Me and Gus (1977 Gus Tomlins ed. Sturm) 73

Date: 0/0/1937
Source: Dictionary of Slang
Author: PARTRIDGE
Vol / Page: 609
Edition:
Quote: <i>Pat (or Pat), on one's</i>. Alone; single-handed: Australian and New Zealand: C. 20. C. J. Dennis, 1916. Ex <i>Pat Malone</i>, q.v. .. <i>Pat.</i> 2. (Gen. pl.) A Chinaman: New Zealand c. (- 1932). Prob. suggested by the relevant sense of <i>John. </i>
