Date: 0/0/1988
Source: Dictionary of Kiwi Slang, A
Author: McGILL
Vol / Page: 82
Edition:
Quote: <i>pat</i>, phr. <i>on one's pat</i> single-handed or alone, short for rhyming slang `on one's Pat Malone/alone' or on your `own'; eg `Since Mabel passed on, Ron's been on his pat for too much. Time we went round and jollied him up, fellas. Agree?' ANZ.
